'''Justin Chung''' is an artist whose work for Star Wars includes illustrating sketch cards for the [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']], ''Star Wars: 30th Anniversary'', ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)]]'', ''Star Wars Galaxy Series Four'', ''[[The Clone Wars: Season One]]'', ''Star Wars Galaxy Series Five'', ''Clone Wars: Rise of the Bounty Hunters'', ''Star Wars Galaxy Series Six'', and ''Star Wars Galactic Files'' trading card sets for [[The Topps Company, Inc.|Topps]]. Justin was invited by Lucasfilm to be a guest at the [[Celebration IV]] Art Show for which he illustrated a limited edition Star Wars print.

The Jedi Knight [[Kai Justiss]], created and frequently illustrated by [[Joe Corroney]], is named after Justin and based on his likeness. Kai Justiss has also been illustrated by [[Jan Duursema]] and [[Chris Trevas]]. Authors that have contributed stories with Kai Justiss include [[Pablo Hidalgo]], [[Abel G. Peña]], [[Daniel Wallace]], and [[John Ostrander]].

Justin is also the creator of the award-winning [http://www.worldfamouscomics.com World Famous Comics]. Online since 1995 and updated daily, this website is one of the Web's first, largest and most frequented destinations for comic book and entertainment fans.

Together, [[Amy Allen]] and Justin run the [http://www.worldfamouscomics.com/amyallen Official Amy Allen Website].

